article.headline: Longwood 79, Liberty 68
article.story: FARMVILLE, Va. (AP) -- Ryan Bogan scored 23 points and Longwood closed the regular season with a 79-68 victory over Liberty on Friday night. Kevin Swecker and Brandon Giles each added 12 points for the Lancers (9-22). A layup and free throw by Alex McLean pulled Liberty (14-14) to 40-39 with 16:11 remaining in the second half, but Kirk Williams made a pair of layups and Swecker hit a 3-pointer to help Longwood pull away. Anthony Smith scored 24 points for the Flames, and McLean had 23. Bogan scored to break a 23-all tie with 5:48 left in the first half and the Lancers entered halftime ahead 35-31.
